{"title_page": "Wide Wide Clipper", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox VG\n|image     = \n|title     = Wide Wide Clipper\n|platforms = [[Arcade game|Arcade]]\n|developer = [[Namco]]\n|publisher=  Namco\n|released  = [[2001 in video gaming|December 2001]]\n|modes     = [[Single player]], [[multi player]]\n}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''''Wide Wide Clipper'''''|\u30ef\u30a4\u30c9\u30ef\u30a4\u30c9\u30af\u30ea\u30c3\u30d1|Waido Waido Kurippa}} is a redemption game developed and released by Namco in 2001. It is based on the company's ''[[Clena-Flex]]'' series of prize machines and would later receive a sequel titled {{nihongo|'''''Wide Wide Clipper Blue Version'''''|\u30ef\u30a4\u30ef\u30a4\u30af\u30ea\u30c3\u30d1\u30fc\u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u30d0\u30fc\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3|Waido Waido Kurippa Bur\u016b B\u0101jon}} in 2002.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bandainamcoent.co.jp/am/prize/widewideclipper_blue/|title=\u30a2\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30ba\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8\u30de\u30b7\u30f3\uff5c\u30ef\u30a4\u30ef\u30a4\u30af\u30ea\u30c3\u30d1\u30fc\u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u30d0\u30fc\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3|website=bandainamcoent.co.jp}}</ref>\n\n==Gameplay==\nThe player must use the three buttons on the control panel to maneuver a crane mounted to the top of the cabinet.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.am-j.co.jp/newmachine/200210/010.html|title=\u30ef\u30a4\u30ef\u30a4\u30af\u30ea\u30c3\u30d1\u30fc \u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u30d0\u30fc\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3|website=www.am-j.co.jp}}</ref> The first button moves the crane forward and backward, the second button moves the crane right, and the third and final button moves the crane left. Once the player lets go of all the buttons, the crane will halt and descend into the cabinet and close, potentially acquiring the prize inside the cabinet. The crane will then rise and move itself towards the prize chute, and the game will be over.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bandainamcoent.co.jp/am/prize/widewideclipper/index.php|title=\u30a2\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30ba\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8\u30de\u30b7\u30f3\uff5c\u30ef\u30a4\u30ef\u30a4\u30af\u30ea\u30c3\u30d1\u30fc|website=bandainamcoent.co.jp}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://bandainamcoent.co.jp/am/prize/widewideclipper/ Bandai Namco corporate press page on the first game]\n\n{{Namco electro mechanical games}}\n\n[[Category:Bandai Namco Entertainment franchises]]\n[[Category:Namco redemption games]]\n[[Category:Namco arcade games]]\n[[Category:2001 video games]]\n[[Category:Redemption games]]\n[[Category:Arcade games]]\n[[Category:Arcade-only games]]\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=September 2017}}\n{{Infobox VG\n|image     = \n|title     = Wide Wide Clipper\n|platforms = [[Arcade game|Arcade]]\n|developer = [[Namco]]\n|publisher=  Namco\n|released  = [[2000 in video gaming|December 2000]]\n|modes     = [[Single player]], [[multi player]]\n}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''''Wide Wide Clipper'''''|\u30ef\u30a4\u30c9\u30ef\u30a4\u30c9\u30af\u30ea\u30c3\u30d1|Waido Waido Kurippa}} is a redemption game developed and released by Namco in 2001. It is based on the company's ''[[Clena-Flex]]'' series of prize machines and would later receive a sequel titled {{nihongo|'''''Wide Wide Clipper Blue Version'''''|\u30ef\u30a4\u30ef\u30a4\u30af\u30ea\u30c3\u30d1\u30fc\u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u30d0\u30fc\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3|Waido Waido Kurippa Bur\u016b B\u0101jon}} in 2002.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bandainamcoent.co.jp/am/prize/widewideclipper_blue/|title=\u30a2\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30ba\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8\u30de\u30b7\u30f3\uff5c\u30ef\u30a4\u30ef\u30a4\u30af\u30ea\u30c3\u30d1\u30fc\u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u30d0\u30fc\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3|website=bandainamcoent.co.jp}}</ref>\n\n==Gameplay==\nThe player must use the three buttons on the control panel to maneuver a crane mounted to the top of the cabinet.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.am-j.co.jp/newmachine/200210/010.html|title=\u30ef\u30a4\u30ef\u30a4\u30af\u30ea\u30c3\u30d1\u30fc \u30d6\u30eb\u30fc\u30d0\u30fc\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3|website=www.am-j.co.jp}}</ref> The first button moves the crane forward and backward, the second button moves the crane right, and the third and final button moves the crane left. Once the player lets go of all the buttons, the crane will halt and descend into the cabinet and close, potentially acquiring the prize inside the cabinet. The crane will then rise and move itself towards the prize chute, and the game will be over.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bandainamcoent.co.jp/am/prize/widewideclipper/index.php|title=\u30a2\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30ba\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8\u30de\u30b7\u30f3\uff5c\u30ef\u30a4\u30ef\u30a4\u30af\u30ea\u30c3\u30d1\u30fc|website=bandainamcoent.co.jp}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://bandainamcoent.co.jp/am/prize/widewideclipper/ Bandai Namco corporate press page on the first game]\n\n{{Namco electro mechanical games}}\n\n[[Category:Bandai Namco Entertainment franchises]]\n[[Category:Namco redemption games]]\n[[Category:Namco arcade games]]\n[[Category:2001 video games]]\n[[Category:Redemption games]]\n[[Category:Arcade games]]\n[[Category:Arcade-only games]]\n", "name_user": "DrDevilFX", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wide_Wide_Clipper"}
