nalgoals1 = 0 | nationalteam1 = [[Estonia national under-17 football team|Estonia U-17]]\n| nationalyears2 =           | nationalcaps2 =  9 | nationalgoals2 = 0 | nationalteam2 = [[Estonia national under-19 football team|Estonia U-19]]\n| nationalyears3 = 2000\u20132005 | nationalcaps3 = 16 | nationalgoals3 = 2 | nationalteam3 = [[Estonia national under-21 football team|Estonia U-21]]\n| nationalyears4 = 2001\u20132013   | nationalcaps4 = 22 | nationalgoals4 = 1 | nationalteam4 = [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jalgpall.ee/news.php?st=style_fp.css&news_id=726|title=K\u00f5ik Eesti internatsionaalid|publisher=[[Eesti Jalgpalli Liit]]|accessdate=11 September 2011|language=Estonian|trans-title=All Estonian internationals}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Jarmo Ahjupera''' (born 13 April 1984) is an [[Estonia]]n professional [[football (soccer)|footballer]]. He plays the position of [[Striker (football)|striker]] and is 1.96 m tall.\n\n==Club career==\nIn 2009 February, Jarmo Ahjupera signed a 3,5-year deal with the Hungarian side [[Gy\u0151ri ETO FC]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sport.postimees.ee/82875/ahjupera-solmis-kinki-ja-sisovi-klubiga-lepingu|title=Ahjupera s\u00f5lmis Kinki ja \u0160i\u0161ovi klubiga lepingu|date=16 February 2009|website=[[Postimees]]}}</ref> On 28 March 2009, in a League Cup match against [[FC Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r]], he suffered broken leg after a late tackle by [[Marko Andi\u0107]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://soccernet.ee/artikkel/jarmo-ahjupera-sai-raskelt-vigastada|title=Jarmo Ahjupera sai raskelt vigastada|website=Soccernet.ee|date=31 March 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2011, he was loaned to [[\u00dajpest FC]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soccernet.ee/eto-laenas-ahjupera-suveni-ujpestile|title=ETO laenas Ahjupera suveni Ujpestile|first=Siim|last=Pulst|date=12 February 2011|website=soccernet.ee}}</ref> where he scored 8 goals in 15 appearances.\n\n==International career==\nWhen making the debut on 4 July 2001, Ahjupera (then aged 17 years and 82 days) became the youngest debutant of [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]].<ref name=\"natdebut\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ohtuleht.ee/419450 |title=V\u00f5imas v\u00f5itleja! |trans-title=Mighty fighter! |language=Estonian |work=[[\u00d5htuleht]] |accessdate=23 May 2011 |date=23 March 2011}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 14 November 2012 in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] against [[United Arab Emirates national football team|United Arab Emirates]], putting the ball firmly into the net after receiving a long pass from midfield by [[Konstantin Vassiljev]].\n\n===International goals===\n:''Scores and results list Estonia's goal tally first.''\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 14 November 2012 || [[Mohammed Bin Zayed Stadium]], [[Abu Dhabi]] || {{fb|United Arab Emirates}} || '''1'''\u20131 || 1\u20132<br /> || [[Exhibition game|Friendly]]\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Club===\n* '''[[FC Valga]]'''\n** [[Esiliiga|Estonian Second Division]]: 2002\n*** Runners Up: 2001\n* '''[[FC Flora Tallinn]]'''\n** [[Meistriliiga|Estonian Top Division]]: 2003\n*** Runners Up: 2007, 2008\n** [[Estonian Cup]]: 2008\n*** Runners Up: 2003, 2006\n** [[Estonian SuperCup]]: 2003, 2004\n*** Runners Up: 2006\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.fcflora.ee/index.php?main_id=11&id=17? Flora FC profile]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ahjupera, Jarmo}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from V\u00f5hma]]\n[[Category:Estonian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Estonia international footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Flora players]]\n[[Category:N\u00f5mme Kalju FC|Players]]\n[[Category:JK Tervis P\u00e4rnu players]]\n[[Category:FC Warrior Valga players]]\n[[Category:Viljandi JK Tulevik players]]\n[[Category:Gy\u0151ri ETO FC players]]\n[[Category:\u00dajpest FC players]]\n[[Category:Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I pla